{"pageProps":{"note":{"id":"q05mk77jlifgc0yc83q9nyi","title":"Text Repl","desc":"","updated":1641428826843,"created":1641428826843,"custom":{},"fname":"s.l.bash.text-manip.text-repl","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":"DevLog"},"contentHash":"fe16e091015f3964a07212855c81ad59","links":[],"anchors":{"text-replacement-in-bash":{"type":"header","text":"Text Replacement In Bash","value":"text-replacement-in-bash","line":9,"column":0,"depth":4}},"children":["fcfuzcgefzlafuqzj7qgatl"],"parent":"vskdo0f3xx6hvt3jsq5z54v","data":{}},"body":"<h1 id=\"text-repl\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#text-repl\"></a>Text Repl</h1>\n<h4 id=\"text-replacement-in-bash\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#text-replacement-in-bash\"></a>Text Replacement In Bash</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Bash tip: instead of spawning an instance of <code>sed</code>, you can do text replacement in \"pure\" Bash like <code>status=\"${status//,/}\"</code>. Breaking that down:</li>\n<li><code>status=</code>   # assign a new value to the Bash variable <code>status</code>.</li>\n<li><code>status=\"${ … }\"</code> # I just always use double quotes when doing parameter (and command) substitution.</li>\n<li><code>status=\"${status … }\"</code> # the new value I am assigning to <code>status</code> is the expansion of (value of) <code>status</code>, BUT first we alter that value…</li>\n<li><code>status=\"${status//PATTERN/STRING}\"</code> # the <code>//</code> means \"globally replace\" (a single <code>/</code> would replace the first occurrence of PATTERN)</li>\n</ul>\n<pre class=\"language-shell\"><code class=\"language-shell\"><span class=\"token assign-left variable\">status</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"<span class=\"token variable\">${status<span class=\"token operator\">/</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span><span class=\"token operator\">,</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>}</span>\"</span>\n<span class=\"token assign-left variable\">status</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"<span class=\"token variable\">${status<span class=\"token operator\">/</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>PATTERN<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>STRING}</span>\"</span>\n\n<span class=\"token assign-left variable\">firstString</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"I love Suzi and Marry, but Suzi Most\"</span>\n<span class=\"token assign-left variable\">secondString</span><span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"Sara\"</span>\n<span class=\"token builtin class-name\">echo</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"<span class=\"token variable\">${firstString<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>Suzi<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>$secondString}</span>\"</span>    <span class=\"token comment\"># prints 'I love Sara and Marry'</span>\n</code></pre>\n<hr>\n<strong>Children</strong>\n<ol>\n<li><a href=\"/DevLog/notes/fcfuzcgefzlafuqzj7qgatl\">Doc</a></li>\n</ol>","noteIndex":{"id":"root","title":"root","desc":"","updated":1641013093667,"created":1595961348801,"stub":false,"custom":{"stub":false,"nav_order":0,"permalink":"/"},"fname":"root","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":"DevLog"},"contentHash":"b0b26527a2962dbb8bd5fb9a53ad702f","links":[],"anchors":{},"children":["rzqe5mjn3q2zfscw1roxr20","Bl9NeJmftBQJyJA3X4a6u","inm1S24v2GcN3Quf7gzDb","fmx7cfcdzale0ezna61yq5z","q6tr8q7gahfijix2ktlhcu3","yah6spesmpstech2ue2k3lq","6pxwlugphnw6vm4t8kn0j5p","i17wi8y2hgivywe08h6q6it","1st35wikvph2aew8aana21u","mijr0wvj3qz0mt9pv9xo1jv","qaf8v120h0ffvbowysjxw50","sh4851li2rsrhx47wwsirgv","fwqjigvqyfxiyl3pbpjvgdw","pxdvvln974xhe8w0alh0hoy","n6yddb1smrac5ll3l1y6wbd","g5dllyqoqkenoiz3opalzu6","kbwt8ucy0yh6bo8fl0kv9iw","beykavbe22agsufmm03hu0c","2uvuqa3c15o5r4j7sqadqvr","yr6gzhx0bhzyec6f52y66vf","4no90tcdswtuwmjm0bxnetx"],"parent":null,"data":{},"body":"\nThe hyperfixated rabbit hole di